<font color="#FF0000">THE PRICE OF  BRASS AND GLORY!</font><br>
<tt>Wed Oct 22 22:27:56 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Oh Yeah!<br>
$6,000,000 to train a pilot? Well you should see what the government spent to get me my Super Dooper can't talk about it, Top Secret military clearance, they spent all that $ and all they had to do was ask my mom.<br>
Guess they figured I was going to stay. When they asked me, I said &quot;I thought about it, laughted about it and forgot about it?&quot;<br>
The police department wanted to use it, but the rules had changed and I wasn't about to play under kiddie rules by then.<br>
Did get an offer from overseas, but they wouldn't pay the price I asked, I mean I just wanted a bonus, wanted them to make me a major, not that it meant anything to me I just like the insignia. <br>
 <br>
Sometimes I swear, the government, could have done the same in deciding which pilots to train and which ones to let go of, I mean when they aren’t looking, you , yell! <br>
Hey, Think Fast and you throw a fast hard ball at them. If they catch it you make them pilots, simple. <br>
In Nam we choose our leaders by asking them if they had a sister, if they did we figured the guy would want to live so that he could get back home to protect his sisters honor and so we made him squad leader.<br><br>

